<taxonomicName authorityName="Bowdich" authorityYear="1821" box="[317,427,1626,1650]" class="Mammalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Carnivora</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[108,636,1676,1733]" lastBlockId="40.[684,1212,1213,1435]" pageId="40">
The known carnivore fauna of the Yavarí- 
<subSubSection pageId="40" type="description">
<collectingRegion box="[108,191,1709,1733]" country="Peru" name="Ucayali" pageId="40">Ucayali</collectingRegion>
interfluve includes 16 species in five families— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1817" box="[798,886,1213,1237]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Canidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer de Waldheim" authorityYear="1817" box="[896,975,1213,1237]" class="Mammalia" family="Felidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Felidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1817" box="[986,1107,1213,1237]" class="Mammalia" family="Mustelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Mustelidae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1825" class="Mammalia" family="Procyonidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="40" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Procyonidae</taxonomicName>
—and it seems unlikely that any additional species will be found in the region. The Matses recognize and name all of the local carnivores, and experienced hunters are familiar with the principal ecobehavioral traits of most species (
<tableCitation box="[775,852,1411,1435]" captionStart="TABLE 8" captionStartId="39.[610,690,226,250]" captionTargetBox="[119,1167,353,1109]" captionText="TABLE 8 Niche Separation among 16 Carnivores of the Yavarí-Ucayali Interfluve according to Matses Informants" pageId="40">table 8</tableCitation>
).
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
